    <div class="block__content">
      <p>During periods of severe cold weather, additional emergency accommodation is provided by the council).</p>
      <p>The Council has signed up to a long standing government protocol to find accommodation for any person who requires it, irrespective of legal duty, when the temperature is forecast to be below zero for two nights in succession.</p>
      <p>The Newark approach <em>exceeds the government protocol described above</em>, in that the arrangements are activated if the temperature is forecast to be below zero for one night and are not suspended until the first standard working day after the temperature has risen above zero. This means that during the period that Severe Weather Provision (SWP) arrangements are in place, no one needs to sleep on the streets of Newark.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


